node.text:
More than the launch of unparalleled works of jewelry craft, @Bulgari's Magnifica High Jewelry collection is a celebration of rebirth. Honored through magnificent muses, music, and Milan, take a look at Bvlgari's latest high jewelry collection.
 
Models: @vittoria, @lilyaldridge @heconghc, @solangesmith and @blesnyaminher
Special Guests: @andreabocelliofficial @beatricevenezi
Project by @oma.eu
Director @tommaso.ottomano
DOP@ mrcodepa
Stylist @sagliogeraldine
Music @guazzonemarco 
Production @studio.april
#Bvlgari #BvlgariJewelry #BvlgariHighJewelry #BvlgariMagnifica #Milan

node.text: After making her #NYFW modeling debut at @ProenzaSchouler, @EllaEmhoff landed a knitwear collaboration with Batsheva Hay (@batshevadress). The 21-year-old student, model, and designer met up with Hay amid NYFW—and #GoodMorningVogue was there to capture their conversations about materials, fit, and texture, plus Ella's rise to fame in the wake of the inauguration of President Joe Biden and Emhoff’s step-mother, Kamala Harris, in January.

node.text: This month, Vogue joined forces with an army of photographers and models all around the globe—stable Zoom connections required, please!—and sent the best and brightest of the new collections via courier services everywhere from Beijing to Brazil, Lagos to Los Angeles. Our concept? Simple, glorious movement: After a year of stasis, immobility and lockdowns, we wanted to see spring fashion breaking free. These are the looks we love, shot by the photographers we adore, on the run and out for a walk, a swim, a dance. Tap the link in our bio to see more.

node.text:
Today, @KamalaHarris became the first woman of color ever sworn in as vice president of the United States.

To celebrate this moment, twelve young women discussing what it means to them to see a Black woman of Indian descent elected to the second-highest office in the land. “Every little girl sees that this is a country of possibility,” @KamalaHarris states in one address, and that sentiment is widely echoed. “She reminds me every day that I am capable and worthy of my wildest dreams,” says one participant.

Director @rombokob
Producer @aliwebb_producer
Casting Director: Rebecca Dealy
Archival Research: Manon Blackman
Editor @ann_lupo
GFX @horatiobaltz
Color @carlosfloresfilms
Mix @cstropko
Post Production @forager.tv

node.title: 12 Girls on What Kamala Harris Becoming Vice President Means to Them

node.text: Throughout the political tumult of 2020, @janayathefuture was one of the most prominent voices to become a source of healing and hope. Reflecting on this week’s events, Khan points out the lack of police presence at the Capitol, a fact that exposes, in their own words, “a clear double standard for how Black protestors have been treated over the past several years. What we know to be true is that there is a way that white rage is celebrated in this country and Black grief is criminalized.” To hear more, make sure to check out Khan’s Sunday Sermons, returning tomorrow 1/10  at 12PM PST on their account.

node.title: @janayathefuture on Moving Forward from the Capitol Riots

node.text:
Congratulations to @penelopecruzoficial for winning the Volpi Cup for Best Actress at the 78th Venice International Film Festival for her performance in "Parallel Mothers." The star accepted her award in a stunning @chanelofficial gown that took an incredible 600 hours to make. 

 Tap the link in bio to see all of the best red carpet moments from the Venice Film Festival.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Vogue on September 12, 2021 tagging @ediebcampbell. May be an image of 1 person, standing and horse.

node.text:
Want to test your relationship with your mother? Design and build a house with her. Model @ediebcampbell and mother Sophie Hicks recently teamed up to construct her Northamptonshire home. Edie adds, “In the past, we’ve had a slightly fractious relationship. You’re always ruder to your mother than you are to your friends. But suddenly we were in this professional situation and we were quite agreeable to each other.” 

Tap the link in bio to learn more about Edie's Northamptonshire homestead and its charming design complete with stables for her many horses.

Photographed by @simonpwatson, styled by @tabithasimmons, Vogue, October 2021

node.text:
Inspired by her travels and favorite tiki haunt, @annasui’s tropical paradise spring 2022 ready-to-wear show was positively filled with cute wantable things. She is always expanding her product offering, and this season she hit almost every note, from rainbow tweed mini suits to floral board shorts to girlish prom dresses.

Tap the link in bio to see all of Anna Sui's spring 2022 ready-to-wear collection.

node.text:
Kacey Musgraves isn’t afraid to get real. The superstar singer-songwriter’s music has always let listeners into her inner world, but her latest album, Star-Crossed, goes further. Penned while Musgraves was divorcing her ex-husband, Ruston Kelly, its exploration of love, grief, and self-discovery is boldly confessional.

Tap the link in bio to discover all you need to know about her new album and more. 

Photos by @yasi

node.text:
There’s only one short day until the 2021 #MetGala!
This year the @metcostumeinstitute’s Met Gala will feature a sustainable plant-based menu, featuring recipes from ten up-and-coming chefs based in New York City—and we’re giving you a sneak peek at who they are and the delicious recipes they have created.

Meet the #MetGalaChefs: In this video we introduce, Lazarus Lynch (@sonofasouthernchef) who demonstrates how to prepare Jerk Corn with Coconut Confetti. Make sure to show us how you cooked like our #MetGalachefs. 
Directed by @jeremyjacobowitz

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Vogue on September 11, 2021 tagging @arnold_daniel. May be an image of one or more people and skyscraper.

node.text:
"September 11 didn’t end in September or October or even in 2011 or 2021. The losses of Covid won’t go away, either—even after the virus has abated (whatever that looks like). But we learn to live with loss and the sharp pain it brings. And New York will continue on."

At the link in our bio, @MollyJongFast reflects on how during both 9/11 and the height of the pandemic, she felt like she couldn’t possibly leave where she was from—as she says, "like being a New Yorker was my identity." Photographed by @arnold_daniel

node.text: Congratulations to @EmmaRaducanu on an incredible win! The 18-year-old British tennis player has won the #USOpen final for her first Grand Slam title. She is the first British woman to win the U.S. Open singles title in 53 years, and the youngest Women's Major Champion in 17 years. Tap the link in our bio to read our profile of the tennis champion. Photographed by @scotttrindle, styled by @poppykain, @britishvogue, October 2021

node.text:
Today, we remember 9/11 on its 20th anniversary. A day Americans, especially New Yorkers, will never forget. 

New York isn’t a landmark or zip code, a coterie of cool people, an art movement, or a moment in time. It is the millions of New Yorkers who give the city its magic. Tap the link in bio as Vogue celebrates everything—and everyone—that makes New York…New York.  Directed by @bardiazeinali.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Vogue on September 10, 2021 tagging @preciousleexoxo, @hunterabrams, and @brandonmaxwell. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text:
@BrandonMaxwell played designer and stylist at his spring 2022 show. “I wanted to do something that felt authentic, he said. “When I started I was maybe insecure about not having a fashion education, so I felt I needed to be more serious. But I’m not that serious a person. During the pandemic, I decided that if I got the opportunity ever again, I’d like to do it as me.” Tap the link in bio to see all the looks.

Photographed by @hunterabrams

Ahead of this year’s #MetGala on September 13th, Anna Wintour is looking back at the event’s most memorable ensembles in a brand new #LifeinLooks video–and these style highlights are definitely worth a revisit. 
From @badgalriri always understanding the assignment to taking a trip down memory lane, watch Wintour look back at the Met Gala's most iconic looks at the link in our bio.

node.text:
Happy Friday! @JLO and @BenAffleck just made their first red carpet appearance as a couple at the Venice Film Festival, and they look better than ever. 

Tap the link in our bio for all of the details, including how J Lo's hairstylist @ChrisAppleton1 achieved her bombshell blowout.
